data.enText: a flat bar on a machine such as a bicycle, car, etc. that you push down with your foot in order to make parts of the machine move or work

data.chText: 我骑她的车够不到脚蹬子。
data.enText: I couldn't reach the pedals on her bike.
She pressed her foot down sharply on the brake pedal.

data.chText: （钢琴、风琴等的）踏板，踏瓣，脚踏键
data.enText: a bar on a musical instrument such as a piano or an organ that you push with your foot in order to control the sound

data.chText: 我看见她在纤道上骑自行车。
data.enText: I saw her pedalling along the towpath.

data.chText: 他跳上自行车就骑走了。
data.enText: He jumped on his bike and pedalled off.
She pedalled her bicycle up the track.
to turn or press the pedals on a bicycle or other machine

data.chText: 走上坡时你必须用力蹬车。
data.enText: You'll have to pedal hard up this hill.

data.chText: 她整个上午都在蹬健身车。
data.enText: She had been pedalling her exercise bike all morning.

simple_means.memory_skill: ped 脚，足 + al …的 → 脚的

tr: a lever that is operated with the foot
operate the pedals on a keyboard instrument
of or relating to the feet
example: the word for a pedal extremity is `foot'

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 pedaling, pedaled

value.def: The pedals on a bicycle are the two parts that you push with your feet in order to make the bicycle move.
When you pedal a bicycle, you push the pedals around with your feet to make it move.

example.ex: She climbed on her bike with a feeling of pride and pedalled the five miles home...
example.tran: 她自豪地骑上自行车，蹬了5英里路回家。

example.ex: She was too tired to pedal back.
example.tran: 她太累了，没力气骑自行车回去。

value.def: A pedal in a car or on a machine is a lever that you press with your foot in order to control the car or machine.

trans: 制动器踏脚板，刹车踏板
